<br>
I'm sure Lobaner might have an opinion on this. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
Great analysis though. If we carry the discussion on a bit farther to the end of the battle, healing is once again 'discouraged' by the current array of spells. <br>
<br>
A few thoughts, from an RP perspective, if we can freely summon the most powerful of elements, then we should be able to infuse (heal) those elements for the same type of ratio with which we summon them.<br>
<br>
If you look at the cost of creating a new pet:<br>
eg:<br>
level 53 air pet has 2350 hp and costs 300 mana to summon.<br>
BOIII = 150 mana<br>
Plate armor = 300 mana<br>
<br>
Level 52 pet heal costs 250 mana per cast, and would take 4 casts to fully heal a pet.<br>
<br>
For those scoring along at home, thats an extra 250 mana down the toilet, where you would actually regain a bit of mana by simply reclaiming, resummoning, and re-equipping.<br>
<br>
For those aspiring to get the Level 60 pet heal, it would take two casts to heal most of the pets hp, and would also take more mana than simply summoning and re-equipping a new pet. <br>
<br>
They way the system is currently set up, these facts do point to nuking/chaining/reclaiming as the way VI seems to want us to go. Its just much tougher for epic mages to do this on a regular basis, and just a lot of extra work for us non-epic mages to do after a fight.<br>
<br>
My suggestion: Add a component based pet heal spell, for the cost of a piece of malachite (okay fine, peridot so as not to infringe upon those with mend companion) , 700 mana, 5min recast, you can CH your pet and allow it to keep its gear/buffs. Also, switch mend companion to a 20 minute timer.<br>
<br>
My Question: I've heard people suggest that VI does not think chaining pets/chain reclaiming is 'appropriate'. Is this hearsay? Or did someone from VI actually post about this at some point? <p>Naladini <BR>
