I came to the same conclusions, Raz.  The pet heals are sub par for mana/time/damage/safety ratios then straight out nuking is.<br>
<br>
Being able to summon 3000+ hp worth of pet for 400 mana, it seems odd that we are constrained to a far, far worse ratio when summoning that same energy to infuse the pet with health.<br>
<br>
What I propose is this:<br>
<br>
Transon's Resurgence of the Elements<br>
Increase pet hp by 1500(61) to 1700(65)<br>
Mana Cost: 400<br>
Cast time: 10 seconds<br>
Reagent cost: 1 Malachite (Elemental Pact would remove this regent)<br>
<br>
This essentially gives us a pet heal that would actually come very close to the nuke in balance of your above ratio.  It is similar to the shaman's new heal in mana cost and time, but not quite as good, and has a reagent cost to represent the greater energy we need to use to bring forth that much elemental power and to balance it VS chainsummoning.  Our version of 'complete heal'.  This spell would also by its very nature reinforce our PoP pets to make them that much more viable in a harsh environment (going by the SpData, PoP is going to have some insane mob AoEs, keeping pet alive will be very hard).<br>
<br>
I always thought it was very odd that a priest could heal an unliving minion of pure elemental energy better then a mage could.<br>
<br>
